  "text": "The consumer group coordinator's state machine in Apache Kafka is implemented across two layers:\n\n**Server-side (Group Coordinator):**\n- `ClassicGroupState.java` defines the core state enum: EMPTY, PREPARING_REBALANCE, COMPLETING_REBALANCE, STABLE, DEAD, with valid transition maps in a static initializer block.\n- `ClassicGroup.java` implements the classic group with `transitionTo()` enforcing valid state transitions, and tracks pending JoinGroup/SyncGroup futures per member.\n- `ClassicGroupMember.java` holds per-member metadata including awaiting rebalance/sync futures.\n- `GroupMetadataManager.java` is the main orchestrator containing `classicGroupJoin()`, `classicGroupSync()`, `classicGroupHeartbeat()`, `prepareRebalance()`, and `maybePrepareRebalanceOrCompleteJoin()` \u2014 driving all state transitions.\n- `ConsumerGroup.java` implements the modern consumer group state machine with `ConsumerGroupState` (ASSIGNING, RECONCILING, STABLE, EMPTY, DEAD).\n- `MemberState.java` (modern) defines server-side member states: STABLE, UNREVOKED_PARTITIONS, UNRELEASED_PARTITIONS.\n- `CurrentAssignmentBuilder.java` is the reconciliation engine for the modern consumer group protocol.\n- `Group.java` and `GroupState.java` define the common interfaces and state enums.\n\n**Client-side:**\n- `AbstractCoordinator.java` contains the client-side state machine with MemberState (UNJOINED, PREPARING_REBALANCE, COMPLETING_REBALANCE, STABLE) and drives `sendJoinGroupRequest()`/`sendSyncGroupRequest()`.\n- `ConsumerCoordinator.java` extends AbstractCoordinator with consumer-specific Join/Sync/Rebalance logic.\n- `MemberState.java` (client) defines the modern client member states: JOINING, RECONCILING, ACKNOWLEDGING, STABLE, FENCED, etc.\n- `AbstractMembershipManager.java` and `ConsumerMembershipManager.java` manage modern consumer membership with state transitions.",
